<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="7" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">810.24/41: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Des Fortes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-28T17:00:00-06:00">June 28,
                                    1939—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>19. Department’s circular June 27, 7 p.m. I have taken up the subject
                            matter of the Department’s instruction with the Foreign Minister who
                            viewed it very sympathetically. The Foreign Minister is referring it to
                            the President upon the latter’s return.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>